{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/forms","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Forms in React Native are just a collection of inputs. Whereas on the web we have a <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;form&gt;</code> element and a submit button, this is not the case in React Native. Let's looks at some of the inputs we have available.</p>\n<h2 id=\"textinput\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#textinput\" aria-label=\"textinput permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>TextInput</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/docs/textinput\">TextInput</a> is probably the most common and frequently used text form in React Native. It is actually incredibly powerful and has a many important features.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://snack.expo.io/@kadikraman/textinput-example\">üîç TextInput examples</a></p>\n<p>Here we have 4 examples of what you can do with TextInput:</p>\n<h4 id=\"basic-text-input\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#basic-text-input\" aria-label=\"basic text input permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basic text input</h4>\n<p>The first input is a basic TextInput with no embellishments. We use 4 props:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">style</code> - adding some padding and a border color for the input to be better visible on the screen. The Text Input has no default styles</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">value</code> - the current value</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">onChangeText</code> - gets called with the new value whenever the user changes the content of the input</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">placeholder</code> - some placeholder text to be displayed when the input is empty</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"number-input\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#number-input\" aria-label=\"number input permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Number input</h4>\n<p>Here we use an additional prop called <code class=\"language-text\">keyboardType</code>. You can use <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/docs/textinput#keyboardtype\">this prop</a> to define what type of input this is. Since we're working on phones, this will define what type of keyboard the user gets to work with.</p>\n<p>The options that work on both iOS and Android are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>default</li>\n<li>number-pad</li>\n<li>decimal-pad</li>\n<li>numeric</li>\n<li>email-address</li>\n<li>phone-pad</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"password-input\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#password-input\" aria-label=\"password input permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Password input</h4>\n<p>For password inputs we don't want to show what the user has types. For this we can use the <code class=\"language-text\">secureTextEntry</code> prop and set it to true (default is false). This ensures the input displays *** instead of the actual content.</p>\n<h4 id=\"multiline-input\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#multiline-input\" aria-label=\"multiline input permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Multiline input</h4>\n<p>For a multiline input, we use <code class=\"language-text\">multiline={true}</code>. This will allow the input to grow infinitely. If we'd like to cap the height of the input on the page, we can also set it to a specific number of lines, e.g. 4 with <code class=\"language-text\">numberOfLines={4}</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"picker\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#picker\" aria-label=\"picker permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Picker</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/docs/picker\">Picker</a> component is an interesting one, because it's looks very different across platforms.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://snack.expo.io/@kadikraman/picker-example\">üîç Picker example</a></p>\n<div style=\"display:flex; flex-direction:row\">\n    <div style=\"width:280px;margin:0 auto;margin-bottom:20px\">\n        <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/react-native-v2/static/03515d66720a2a19c4cac4bf497555bd/55d53/picker-ios.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 216.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Style challenge iOS\" title=\"Style challenge iOS\" src=\"/react-native-v2/static/03515d66720a2a19c4cac4bf497555bd/acfc1/picker-ios.png\" srcset=\"/react-native-v2/static/03515d66720a2a19c4cac4bf497555bd/59afc/picker-ios.png 200w,\n/react-native-v2/static/03515d66720a2a19c4cac4bf497555bd/a45af/picker-ios.png 400w,\n/react-native-v2/static/03515d66720a2a19c4cac4bf497555bd/acfc1/picker-ios.png 800w,\n/react-native-v2/static/03515d66720a2a19c4cac4bf497555bd/55d53/picker-ios.png 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"width:300px;margin:0 auto;margin-bottom:20px\">\n        <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 614px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/react-native-v2/static/e42091bb0c48ff2567d311e5c2bb9c1a/c2d66/picker-android.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 198.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Style challenge Android\" title=\"Style challenge Android\" src=\"/react-native-v2/static/e42091bb0c48ff2567d311e5c2bb9c1a/c2d66/picker-android.png\" srcset=\"/react-native-v2/static/e42091bb0c48ff2567d311e5c2bb9c1a/59afc/picker-android.png 200w,\n/react-native-v2/static/e42091bb0c48ff2567d311e5c2bb9c1a/a45af/picker-android.png 400w,\n/react-native-v2/static/e42091bb0c48ff2567d311e5c2bb9c1a/c2d66/picker-android.png 614w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<p>As you can see, the iOS picker is an inline wheel, and the Android picker is a modal! You'll come across these types of UX issues every now and then with React Native. It's great that we can use one codebase to build two fully native apps, but we still have to spend time to learn and explore environment-specific nuances in both platforms.</p>\n<h2 id=\"switch\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#switch\" aria-label=\"switch permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Switch</h2>\n<p>A <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/docs/switch\">Switch</a> is essentially a toggle button. Some styling nuances aside, it looks quite similar across platforms.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://snack.expo.io/@kadikraman/switch-example\">üîç Switch example</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"other-components\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#other-components\" aria-label=\"other components permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other components</h2>\n<p>We have now played around with the most important components built into the core React Native library, but there are loads of community components you can install separately and use!</p>\n<p>If you want to find some more, head over the <a href=\"https://reactnative.directory/\">React Native Directory</a> website.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/forms","title":"Overview of Forms in React Native","order":25}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":0,"path":"/intro","title":"Welcome"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":1,"path":"/react-native","title":"About React Native"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":2,"path":"/the-expo-de